Conftest dot p-y — sharing fixtures.

A conftest dot p-y file is a special py-test file. Any fixtures defined in it are visible to every test file in the same directory and below, with no imports needed.

Use it for fixtures that span many test files — a database connection, a client for testing a flask or fast-a-p-i app, a base config dict.

Picture a tests directory with conftest dot p-y for fixtures spanning everything. An api subdirectory with its own conftest dot p-y for api-only fixtures, plus its test files. A db subdirectory with its test files.

Conftest dot p-y runs implicitly — py-test discovers and loads it before running tests. Never import from it directly.
